    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Front Cover and Related Components -
        Removal - Vibration Damper, Hub, and Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>Vibration Damper, Hub, and Wear Sleeve</title>
        <figure id="f2650614" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh07/h07015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Vibration damper</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration damper</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M10 x 20 (6)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six bolts (M10 x 20) securing the vibration damper to the hub assembly and remove
                the vibration damper.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650615" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh07/h07017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Removing the damper hub assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the damper hub assembly with an H-bar puller and two bolts (M10 x 80).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650616" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh07/h07027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Removing the wear sleeve with a muffler chisel</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Muffler Chisel</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration damper hub</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wear Sleeve</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Split the wear sleeve with a muffler chisel to remove it from the damper. Be careful not to
                damage the vibration damper hub.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If your service kit contains more than one wear sleeve, use the sleeve that has the same width as
                    the current wear sleeve located on the vibration damper hub.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650617" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh07/h07028.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Pressing on the wear sleeve and seal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Arbor press ram</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wear sleeve installer</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wear sleeve seal (570 engines only)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Vibration damper hub</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The chamfer on the wear sleeve outside diameter must be facing in, towards the crankshaft.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply hydraulic sealant sparingly to the inside diameter of a new wear sleeve. Use the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_144.xml" xrefid="t2650603" appearance="hottext">wear sleeve installer
                </hotlnk>
                to press wear sleeve onto the vibration damper hub. Wipe any excess sealant from the outside diameter of
                the wear sleeve.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the same procedure for the wear sleeve and dust lip (POSE) assemblies where
                applicable.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Do not remove the POSE seal from wear sleeve on DT 570 and HT 570 engines.</para>
                <para>The front POSE seal is not used on DT 466 or HT 466 engines.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
